Project Origins:::
The inspiration for this project was sparked by the film Interstellar. A deep fascination with blackhole theory evolved from simple curiosity 
into a rigorous research mission to explore the limits of information and data integrity. What began as a personal study grew into a larger 
exploration of how AI handles information: specifically, the distinction between what I call "Pure" and "Impure" data.

Project Roadmap:::
Phase I (Data Synthesis): Development of the TREE Method to extract 215 pages of comprehensive data on blackholes using AI as a foundational tool.
Phase II (Analysis)     : Evaluation of AI efficiency in generating accurate information compared to standard "low-effort" prompting.
Phase III (Verification): Implementation of the MPDVCO Method to audit and calculate the "purity" of the synthesized dataset.

Methodologies in Action::: 
1. Data Extraction: The TREE Method (Trunk-Branch-Leaf)
        This is a structured, hierarchical prompting framework designed to ensure exhaustive data coverage without information gaps.
              TRUNK (Major Topics)  : Identification and documentation of all major blackhole research categories established as of Summer 2025.
              BRANCH (Sub-Topics)   : Breaking down each major category into its constituent sub-topics for analysis.
              LEAF (Data Extraction): Sequential extraction of detailed information for every sub-topic, ensuring a logical and continuous flow of data.

2. Data Verification: The MPDVCO Method (Manual-Pure Data-Verification-and-Calculation-in-Order) 
        The Manual-Pure Data-Verification-and-Calculation-in-Order method is used to audit the synthetic data against verified human knowledge.
              SEARCH      : Identifying authoritative sources (such as Wikipedia) for every minor topic in the dataset.
              VERIFICATION: A manual comparison in an ordely manner between the AI-generated data and trusted sources to ensure factual accuracy.
              CALCULATION : Quantifying the "Purity Percentage" by comparing the efficiency of the TREE Method against standard prompting techniques in ChatGPT-4.

Conclusion:::
The TREE and MPDVCO methods represent a personal, systematic solution to the global challenge of data impurity. By combining hierarchical extraction with rigorous 
manual auditing, this project provides a blueprint for generating high-fidelity information in the age of AI. 

